FuncDef: The cut access-user command terminates one or multiple access user connections, that is, disconnecting online users.
CLIs: cut access-user { domain <domain-name> | ip-address <ip-address> [ vpn-instance <vpn-instance-name> ] | ipv6-address <ipv6-address> | service-scheme <service-scheme-name> | user-id <begin-number> [ <end-number> ] | username <user-name> }
cut access-user access-type { admin [ ftp | ssh | telnet | terminal | http ] } [ username <user-name> ]
cut access-user access-type { admin [ ftp | ssh | telnet | terminal | http | md-cli | snmp ] } [ username <user-name> ]
cut access-user authentication-mode { all | hwtacacs | local | radius | ldap }
cut access-user { domain <domain-name> | ip-address <ip-address> | service-scheme <service-scheme-name> | user-id <begin-number> [ <end-number> ] | username <user-name> }

ParaDef.Info:
Indicates all authentication modes.
-

Indicates the HWTACACS authentication mode.
-

Indicates the local authentication mode.
-

Indicates the RADIUS authentication mode.
-

Indicates the user authentication mode.
-

Indicates the LDAP authentication mode.
-

Disconnects sessions in a specified domain.
The domain must already exist.

Disconnects sessions initiated by a specified IP address.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Indicates the name of a VPN instance to which the specified IP address belongs. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6860-SAN, CE6866K, CE6866, CE6860-HAM, CE6855-48XS8CQ, CE6885-SAN, CE8850-SAN, CE8855, CE8851-32CQ4BQ, CE8851K, CE8851-32CQ8DQ-P, CE8850-HAM, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K, CE6820S, CE6885, CE6885-T, CE6885-LL (standard forwarding mode) and CE6863E-48S8CQ.
The value is a string of 1 to 31 case-sensitive characters without spaces. The VPN instance name cannot be _public_. If the character string is quoted by double quotation marks, the character string can contain spaces.

Displays information about the user with a specified IPv6 address. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6860-SAN, CE6866K, CE6866, CE6860-HAM, CE6855-48XS8CQ, CE6885-SAN, CE8850-SAN, CE8855, CE8851-32CQ4BQ, CE8851K, CE8851-32CQ8DQ-P, CE8850-HAM, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K, CE6820S, CE6885, CE6885-T, CE6885-LL (standard forwarding mode) and CE6863E-48S8CQ.
The value is a 32-digit hexadecimal number in the format X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.

Terminates connections based on the service scheme.
The value is a string of 1 to 32 case-sensitive characters. It cannot contain spaces.

Specifies the start ID of the session to be disconnected.
The user-id must exist on the device.

Specifies the end ID of the session to be disconnected.
The user-id must exist on the device.

Displays information about the users using the specified authentication mode.
The value is a string of 1 to 253 case-sensitive characters.

Indicates the user access type.
-

Indicates information about the administrators using the specified authentication mode.
-

Indicates FTP users.
-

Indicates SSH users.
-

Indicates Telnet users.
-

Indicates terminal users.
-

Indicates HTTP authentication users.
-

Indicates MD-CLI users.
-

Indicates SNMP users.
-

Disconnects sessions initiated by a specified MAC address. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
The value is in the format of H-H-H, in which each H is a hexadecimal number of 1 to 4 digits, such as 00e0 and fc01. If an H contains fewer than 4 digits, the left-most digits are padded with zeros. For example, e0 is displayed as 00e0. The MAC address cannot be set to FFFF-FFFF-FFFF.

Specifies a slot ID. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
The value is an integer.

Displays 802.1X authentication information of a specified interface. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
The value is a string of 1 to 255 case-sensitive characters. It cannot contain spaces.

Specifies an interface name. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
-

Specifies the source interface number. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
-

Indicates the user VLAN. 

 NOTE: 

This parameter is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
The value is an integer ranging from 1 to 4094.

ExtraInfo: Performing some configurations, such as AAA, on the device, requires that no users be online. You can run the cut access-user command to disconnect sessions.
